Investment Title: NOAA/NESDIS/ Comprehensive Large Array-data Stewardship System (CLASS)

Contract Description (USAspending): MISSION SUPPORT SERVICES FOR NOAA'S NCDC, ASHEVILLE, NC.

The purpose of this contract is to develop the ground system that will support NOAA  s next generation geostationary satellite series, GOES-R. This new series of spacecraft, set to begin launching in 2015, is expected to double the clarity of today  s satellite imagery and provide at least 20 times more atmospheric observations from space. The contractor is to design, develop, test and implement the GOES-R ground system. The ground system will capture data from the GOES-R satellites, and process and distribute the information to operational users.

The contract is for the GOES-R Ground Segment Antenna System. The antenna system includes the components and infrastructure needed to communicate with the GOES-R satellites in order to control the satellites and capture the telemetry and science data from the GOES-R instruments.

This contract will provide for support of complete telephone systems. The systems include Nortel Network SL-100 and SL-1 Telephone Systems, CS2100 Systems, other vendor telephone management systems, digital conferencing systems, Automated Centralized Operations and Maintenance Systems (ACOMS), Automated Dial Assistance Service (ADAS), Integrated Service Digital Network (ISDN) applications and products, accessory hardware, proprietary instruments and peripherals. Required services include: commercial level support, labor,remote diagnostics, software support & upgrades, parts & materials, hardware upgrades and enhancements, repair, return and parts replacement, training, warranty, commissioning services, technical support of hardware and software baselines, hardware de-installation, installation, relocation, consulting, extended service plan, services and technical documentation. The contractor will be responsible for integration of all the products and services into the Nortel Networks Telephone Systems.

THE PURPOSE OF THIS CONTRACT IS TO PROVIDE COMPUTER SYSTEM MANAGEMENT, INCLUDING THE OPERATING SYSTEM AND APPLICATION SOFTWARE, THE DEVELOPMENT AND USE OF SCIENTIFIC AND ENGINEERING DATA ANALYSIS SYSTEMS, AND THE ENGINEERING EFFORTS THAT DEVELOP NEW TECHNOLOGY FOR SCIENTIFIC INSTRUMENTATION FOR SPACE AND EARTH SCIENCES RESEARCH AT THE GSFC.

THE SOFTWARE INTEGRATION AND VISUALIZATION OFFICE (SIVO) AT THE NASA GODDARD SPACE FLIGHT CENTER IS TASKED WITH ENABLING SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH BY OFFERING LEADERSHIP TO THE SCIENCE COMMUNITY IN THE AREAS OF:-  SOFTWARE DESIGN FOR HIGH PERFORMANCE COMPUTING-  COMPUTER SCIENCE RESEARCH AND APPLIED NUMERICAL METHODS-  SOFTWARE ENGINEERING TECHNIQUES CATERED TO RESEARCH-  ADVANCED VISUALIZATION TECHNOLOGIES THE COMMUNITY OF EARTH AND SPACE SCIENTISTS AT THE NASA GODDARD SPACE FLIGHT CENTER AND ITS AFFILIATED INSTITUTIONS INCLUDES A CADRE OF RESEARCHERS THAT USE HIGH PERFORMANCE COMPUTERS AS A TOOL OF THEIR INVESTIGATIONS.  VERY LARGE NUMERICAL MODELS OF PHYSICAL SYSTEMS ALLOW THE REPRESENTATION AND ANALYSIS OF PHENOMENA THAT CANNOT BE INVESTIGATED BY DIRECT OBSERVATION, EXPERIMENTATION, OR ANY OTHER MEANS.  AN EXAMPLE OF THIS TYPE OF RESEARCH THAT IS ONGOING AT GODDARD IS NUMERICAL CLIMATE PREDICTION, WHICH GENERATES A LARGE WORKLOAD ON GODDARD'S EXISTING HIGH PERFORMANCE COMPUTER SYSTEMS.THE HIGH PERFORMANCE COMPUTER USER COMMUNITY GLOBALLY AND ACADEMIC AND INDUSTRY EXPERTS ALL AGREE THAT THE MOST IMPORTANT CHALLENGE IN HIGH END COMPUTING IS NOT THE DEVELOPMENT OF LARGER, FASTER HARDWARE, BUT RATHER SYSTEM AND APPLICATION SOFTWARE THAT CAN MAKE THE BEST USE OF THESE DEVICES.SIVO WILL FOCUS ON INCREASING SUPPORT TO THE CUSTOMERS OF HIGH-PERFORMANCE COMPUTING HARDWARE IN THE FOLLOWING AREAS:  -  APPLICATION SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT AND MAINTENANCE (E.G., WRITING NEW APPLICATIONS, WRITING NEW MODULES FOR EXISTING APPLICATIONS, MAINTAINING CODE TO SUPPORT MODIFICATIONS TO APPLICATION PROGRAMMING INTERFACES, MAINTAINING CODE TO CONFORM TO NEW OR MODIFIED OUTPUT DATA FORMATS, ETC.); -  PERFORMANCE TUNING (E.G., DECREASING JOB TURNAROUND TIME, DECREASING JOB HARDWARE RESOURCE REQUIREMENTS, INTRODUCING AND/OR ENHANCING USE OF PARALLEL PROCESSING FACILITIES, ETC.);-  SOFTWARE ENGINEERING (E.G., REWRITING CODE TO BE MORE STRUCTURED AND/OR MODULAR, REWRITING CODE TO OBJECT-ORIENTED STANDARDS, REWRITING APPLICATIONS TO CONFORM TO THE ESMF INTERFACE STANDARDS, TEACHING AND CONSULTING WITH USERS TO THE SAME ENDS, DOCUMENTING CODE, ETC.);-  MIGRATION AND CONVERSION (E.G., PORTING CODE FROM ONE HARDWARE AND/OR OPERATING SYSTEM PLATFORM TO ANOTHER, MIGRATING CODE TO A CONFORM TO A NEW OR DIFFERENT COMPILER, CONVERTING CODE TO BETTER EXPLOIT A MODIFIED FILE SYSTEM OR HIERARCHICAL STORAGE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM, BUILDING INTERFACES TO EMERGING PORTALS AND OTHER FACILITIES, ETC.); AND-  ALLIED TECHNICAL SERVICES.  ALLIED TECHNICAL SERVICES IS A REFERENCE TO THE FACT THAT SIVO CUSTOMERS NOT ONLY NEED SUPPORT IN THE SPECIFIC AREAS OF SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT AND MAINTENANCE, PERFORMANCE TUNING, SOFTWARE MODERNIZATION, PLATFORM INDEPENDENCE, ETC., BUT REQUIRE A COMPLETE SYSTEM SOLUTION IN WHICH COMBINATIONS OF SUPPORT IN THESE AREAS ARE APPLIED.THE PRIMARY PURPOSE OF THIS CONTRACT IS TO PROVIDE THESE SERVICES.A SECONDARY PURPOSE OF THIS CONTRACT IS TO PROVIDE ANCILLARY SYSTEM AND APPLICATION PROGRAMMING AND TECHNICAL SERVICES THAT SUPPORT THE PRIMARY PURPOSE.

Contract Description (USAspending): THE FACILITIES DEVELOPMENT AND OPERATIONS CONTRACT(FDOC) SPECIFIES TECHNICAL, MANAGERIAL, AND ADMINSTRATIVE WORK NEEDED TO ENSURE THE AVAILABLITITY, INTEGRITY, AND RELIABILITY OF MISSIONOPERATIONS FACILITES SUPPORTING NATIONAL AERONAUTICS AND SPACE ADMINISTRATION (NASA) HUMAN SPACE FLIGHT (HSF) PROGRAMS REQUIRING MISSION OPERATIONS SUPPORT. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS CONTRACT IS TO CONSOLIDATE EFFORTS ACROSS THE FACILITIES COVERED UNDER FODOC IN ORDER TO MAXIMIZE SYNERGY FOR HARDWARE AND SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT, MODIFICATION, SUSTAINING. MAINTENANCE, RECONFIGURATION, AND OPERATIONS FOR THE PURPOSE OF REDUCING COST WITHOUT COMPROMISING FACILITY FUNCTIONALITY AND PERFORMANCE. NASA WILL COLLABORATE WITH THE CONTRACTOR ON DEVELOPING PROCEDURAL AND TECHNICAL INNOVATIONS THAT IMPROVE QUALITY, ENSURE CUSTOMER SATISFACTION AND REDUCE COST. MISSION OPERATIONS FACILITIES CURRENTLY SUPPORT THE SPACE SHUTTLE PROGRAMAND THE INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION PROGRA, INCLUDING INTERNATIONAL PARTNER AND COMMMERCIAL VISITING VEHICLES. MISSION OPERATIONS FACILITIES SUPPORTING THE CNSTELLATION PROGRAM(CXP) ARE CONTINUOUSLY UNDER DEVELOPMENT IN CONCERT WITH CXP FORMULATION AND IMPLEMENTATION. FDOC APPLIES TO THE FACILITIES OF THESE THREE PROGRAMS, AND ANY OTHER HSF PROGRAM REQUIRING MISSION OPERATIONS FACILITY SUPPORT. IN ADDITION, FUTURE MISSION OPERATIONS FACILITIES AND CAPABILITIES ARE WITHIN THE TECHNICAL SCOPE OF THIS SOW, AND FDOC WORLK ASSOCIATED WITH THESE FACILITIES WILL BE ENABLED THROUGH IDIQ./INCREMENTAL FUNDING.
